    <item>
      <title>The Gardener and the Carpenter — Alison Gopnik</title>
      <description>Two hosts break down Alison Gopnik's argument that 'parenting' is the wrong model: kids aren't chairs you sculpt, they're gardens you tend. Covers the carpenter vs gardener metaphor, alloparenting, why pretend play is counterfactual reasoning, and why later frontal-lobe maturation correlates with higher IQ.</description>
